3 . She became a very popular saint in the Middle Ages. Her name was early associated with Latin <i>agnus</i> ‘lamb’, leading to the consistent dropping of the initial <i>H-</i> and to her representation in art accompanied by a lamb. The colloquial form <i>Annes</i> led to some confusion with <i>Ann(e)</i> in earlier centuries. Frequent in the medieval period, the name was revived in the 19th century, and has been especially popular in Scotland.  See also  Annis ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Agnes Basset married Robert le Brus about 1086, in Europe. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter."},"et":{"–":"Surnud","1066–1094":"1066–1094","1094–Female":"1094–Surnud","–Female":"Surnud","1066":"1066","about 1086":"umbes 1086","before 1094":"enne 1094","1094":"1094","Europe":"Europe","Branston, Leicestershire, England":"Branston, Leicestershire, England"},"fi":{"–":"Kuollut","1066–1094":"1066–1094","1094–Female":"1094–Kuollut","–Female":"Kuollut","1066":"1066","about 1086":"noin 1086","before 1094":"ennen vuotta 1094","1094":"1094","Europe":"Europe","Branston, Leicestershire, England":"Branston, Leicestershire, England"},"fr":{"–":"Décédée","1066–1094":"1066–1094","1094–Female":"1094–Décédée","–Female":"Décédée","1066":"1066","about 1086":"environ 1086","before 1094":"avant 1094","1094":"1094","Europe":"Europe","Branston, Leicestershire, England":"Branston, Leicestershire, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Agnes Basset a épousé Robert le Brus environ 1086, à Europe. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fille."},"de":{"–":"Verstorben","1066–1094":"1066–1094","1094–Female":"1094–Verstorben","–Female":"Verstorben","1066":"1066","about 1086":"um 1086","before 1094":"vor 1094","1094":"1094","Europe":"Europa","Branston, Leicestershire, England":"Branston, Leicestershire, England","lifeSummary":"Agnes Basset hat um 1086 in Europa Robert le Brus geheiratet. Sie hatten mindestens 1 Tochter."},"ht":{"–":"Desede","1066–1094":"1066–1094","1094–Female":"1094–Desede","–Female":"Desede","1066":"1066"